## Skill Chains

Pick the most relevant 1-2:

- **Research just ran, strong fit** → "Run /pitch-research in **Pitch prep** mode the day before the meeting."
- **Pitch closed (won or lost)** → "Run **Log outcome** mode. Outcomes here will sharpen every future pitch in this category combination."

## Edge Cases
- **Prospect is a current client's competitor** → Flag prominently. Adjacency Check becomes a risk section.
- **No web results at all** → Use training data, label as potentially outdated. Lean on team adjacencies as the only real signal.
- **No brain configured** → Works but without case study backing, adjacency check, or past pitch learnings. Flag prominently.
- **Existing dossier >90 days old** → Refuse fresh Research, route to Refresh mode.
- **User wants to research a prospect they already pitched and lost** → Pull the existing dossier, surface the loss reason, ask whether to attempt re-engagement (likely needs a different angle).

### What this skill can't do

This research uses public sources. With a deeper integration, this skill could
also surface internal knowledge — past interactions captured in CRM, who in
your network knows them, attendance at the same conferences, and live tracking
of when they post a brief. The Brain enables some of this; deeper integrations
unlock the rest.

